abstract: Sales rose 37 percent as demand for corporate software and a more robust economy helped all sectors of the company.
snippet: Sales rose 37 percent as demand for corporate software and a more robust economy helped all sectors of the company.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Oracle, the business software maker, reported yet another quarter of strong gains on Thursday, as corporate spending on its software accelerated in a more robust economy.

headline.main: Strong Software Sales Drive Oracle’s Profit Up 78%
headline.print_headline: Strong Software Sales Drive Oracle’s Profit Up 78%
